Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.34,0:01:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,With high hopes, humans\Nleave Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.61,0:01:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,...to begin a new life in\Nthe space colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.42,0:01:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But the United Earth Sphere\NAlliance gains military power...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.35,0:01:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,...and in the name of\NJustice and Peace...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.36,0:01:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,...seizes control of one\Ncolony after the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.56,0:01:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The year is After Colony 195.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.60,0:01:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Operation Meteor.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.83,0:01:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,To counter the Alliance's\Ntyranny, rebel colonists...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.37,0:01:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,...bring new arsenals\Nto the Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.41,0:01:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,...disguising them as\Nshooting stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.64,0:02:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Alliance headquarters\Ncatches on to this operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.72,0:02:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I shouldn't be\Nfighting each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.26,0:02:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Put your hands down.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.59,0:02:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the first one to surrender\Nand come out, remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.36,0:02:23.14,Wing Episode Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,717.75)\be7\blur6.75}The Victoria Nightmare
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.25,0:02:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We have word on\Nthe Corsica Factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.62,0:02:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemies left before the\Nreinforcements arrived...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.22,0:02:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,...and 55% of the facility\Nis destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.86,0:02:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Walker.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.16,0:02:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for filling me in on\Nanother two enemy machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.96,0:02:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Lieutenant Zechs, Victoria Base{\i0}\N{\i1}is on the line.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.27,0:02:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's been a while,{\i0}\N{\i1}Lieutenant Zechs.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.57,0:02:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Looking good, Noin.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.17,0:03:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear you're pretty busy\Nthese days.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.67,0:03:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Rumors about the\N"Lightning Count"...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.14,0:03:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,...have made it down\Nhere to Victoria.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.11,0:03:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't appreciate the rumors.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.05,0:03:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Enemies target me, and allies{\i0}\N{\i1}expect more than I can handle.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.35,0:03:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Rumors are great.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.39,0:03:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Heard any rumors about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.69,0:03:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I hear you've done well{\i0}\N{\i1}training pilots for outer space.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.53,0:03:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Also that you're a superior{\i0}\N{\i1}all-round soldier.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.70,0:03:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But Noin.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.87,0:03:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You used to hate wars.\N{\i1}What's with all this effort?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.84,0:03:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm honored that you\Nremember so much about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.54,0:03:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My efforts stem from\Nmy love of outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.39,0:03:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,100 meters below surface!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.19,0:03:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Zero G!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.42,0:03:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.29,0:03:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Commence final testing for\Nspace mobile suit operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.96,0:03:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.60,0:03:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.03,0:04:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't have\Nproblems at this speed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.33,0:04:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sense the movements\Nof your ally craft!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.30,0:04:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Zechs is coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.14,0:04:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't embarrass yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.04,0:04:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Zechs is coming?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.91,0:04:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ma'am! I'll do my best!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.38,0:04:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.88,0:04:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.35,0:04:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been one year and\Ntwenty-two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.97,0:04:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've lost him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.57,0:04:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.87,0:04:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the only mobile suit we've\Nconfirmed the location of...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.91,0:04:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,...and it vanished past\Nthe equator.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.28,0:04:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He's headed for the Taurus\Nsuits at Noin's base.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.81,0:04:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The military's too imprudent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.78,0:04:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Even civilian children know\Nthe Taurus space mobile suits...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.69,0:04:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,...are manufactured\Nat the Victoria Base.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.92,0:04:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm on my way over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.72,0:04:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Noin's the only one who'll\Nwelcome an annoying lieutenant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.66,0:05:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You two were old schoolmates\Nthere, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.90,0:05:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm surprised you knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.33,0:05:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.93,0:05:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone knows the top two\Nstudents of all graduates...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.37,0:05:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,...from the Lake Victoria\NMilitary Academy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.81,0:05:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I also know that you\Nwere the top student.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.94,0:05:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,She was always trying\Nto be second.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.05,0:05:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To make me look better.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.65,0:05:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,She might be helping\Nme once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.56,0:05:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs Merquise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.33,0:05:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Or rather, Peacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.67,0:05:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here and lean on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.97,0:05:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's your last day\Nof training.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.91,0:05:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You've followed my\Nstrict command.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.31,0:05:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Today you'll become a member\Nof the elite Specials force.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.13,0:06:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy's after your\Nspace mission Taurus suits!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.00,0:06:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And your first mission\Nas a member of OZ...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.21,0:06:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,...is to get your suits\Noff the base!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.28,0:06:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that a job for\Nthe transport crew?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.72,0:06:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The men I trained can take\Ncare of their own machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.65,0:06:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare to leave immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.52,0:06:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a move on!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.72,0:06:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.27,0:06:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,When will we slip\Nthe Tauruses out?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.30,0:06:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,0700 hours tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.97,0:06:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's cutting it close.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.51,0:06:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard the enemies\Nwon't show on radar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.54,0:06:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got extra soldiers\Non the lookout.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.75,0:06:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the best strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.48,0:07:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Good thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.75,0:07:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate the compliment,\NLieutenant Zechs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.25,0:07:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Call me Zechs, Noin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.55,0:07:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This room sure is cheery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.42,0:07:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of my soldiers are\Nyoung and restless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.99,0:07:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This suits them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.96,0:07:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get too attached\Nor parting will be hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.93,0:07:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for being so concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.23,0:07:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But my soldiers aren't ever\Ngonna be killed in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.50,0:07:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They've been trained not\Nto overdo things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.34,0:07:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, there's no comparing\Nthe value of life versus war.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.28,0:07:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,My soldiers have died.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.38,0:07:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Noin, I disagree with\Nyour philosophy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.52,0:07:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Battles that risk men's lives\Nare pure miscalculations!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.05,0:07:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I pity the soldiers\Nwho get killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.59,0:07:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Noin here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.60,0:07:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs, you've got a call\Nfrom Lieutenant Otto.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.74,0:07:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The technicians are\Njust as surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.27,0:07:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This suit is far more superior\Nthan initially predicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.71,0:08:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It should be ready sooner\Nthan expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.68,0:08:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, it'll take\Nanother month or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.95,0:08:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I see; sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.45,0:08:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep me posted.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.45,0:08:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.79,0:08:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We're under attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.85,0:08:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The pilot trainee dormitory\Nwas hit the worst!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.62,0:08:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.06,0:08:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-This is terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.23,0:08:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I-Instructor...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.37,0:09:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to go to outer\Nspace so badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.01,0:09:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Find the enemy and\Nattack them on sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.84,0:09:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Destroy them!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.91,0:09:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We're expecting a mobile\Nsuit battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.84,0:09:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Leos, lead the pack!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.55,0:09:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy should be close by!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.92,0:09:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How's Lieutenant Zechs?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.42,0:09:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He's safe at the south hangar\Nand now coming over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.32,0:09:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.36,0:09:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy's come to\Ndestroy the Taurus suits!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.76,0:09:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Assume positions!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.79,0:09:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll take 30 minutes to load\Nall the suits for transport.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.83,0:09:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.56,0:09:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold the enemy off\Nfor 30 minutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.80,0:09:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll command the\Nmobile suit troops!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.24,0:09:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No sign of the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.54,0:09:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No enemies at the east gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.34,0:09:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No problems at the water\Npressure generator!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.65,0:09:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No sign of the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.99,0:09:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the enemy hiding?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.92,0:09:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring up the heat\Nsensor images!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.66,0:10:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.83,0:10:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Get some Aries over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.40,0:10:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Only those closest by!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.97,0:10:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going after him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.71,0:10:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Stop! Stop or I'll shoot!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.88,0:10:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll never escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.45,0:10:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Has he got backup?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.92,0:10:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,A Gundam!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.56,0:10:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A Gundam might be waiting\Nwhere the enemy's headed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.33,0:10:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring out the space laser!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.10,0:10:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But we can't fully deploy the{\i0}\N{\i1}heat when it's used on Earth!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.33,0:10:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.27,0:10:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- We just need one shot!\N- Yes ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.41,0:10:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Noin's in enemy pursuit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.78,0:10:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He's heading for the\Nbushes up ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.01,0:10:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a dead end!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.07,0:11:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You coward, attacking soldiers{\i0}\N{\i1}instead of mobile suits!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.34,0:11:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Call yourself a man?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.11,0:11:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You sound like a real\Nknow-it-all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.51,0:11:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He's practically a baby!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.61,0:11:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A kid did all that damage to{\i0}\N{\i1}the base by himself?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.55,0:11:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? A woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.02,0:11:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.47,0:11:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He attacked the base\Non his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.87,0:11:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But he only looks about 14.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.60,0:11:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He's there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.42,0:12:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Target in sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.29,0:12:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.36,0:12:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.33,0:12:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not, Lieutenant Noin?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.39,0:12:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because she's a woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.27,0:12:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.31,0:12:36.75,Wing Series Mid-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(846,382.5)}Mobile Suit Gundam Wing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.16,0:12:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.03,0:12:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Lift off as soon as we get\Nall six Taurus suits loaded!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.30,0:12:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Orders from Lieutenant Noin!\NHurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.70,0:12:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy isn't headed\Nthis way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.77,0:12:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.74,0:12:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll handle things at the base.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.44,0:12:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Just move your aircraft out\Nfrom in front of Transport No. 1!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.97,0:12:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care if you're following\NInstructor Noin's orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.58,0:12:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy isn't coming,\Nso don't move the Taurus suits.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.15,0:13:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.08,0:13:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Get Transport No. 2 out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.75,0:13:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Zechs, I could\Nget you court-martialed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.32,0:13:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm much more composed\Nthan you right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.69,0:13:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If one makes a decision\Nwith a cool head...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.19,0:13:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,...he won't regret\Nhis decision later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.45,0:13:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Move!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.61,0:13:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with you, Aries?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.20,0:13:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-The Taurus suits!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.01,0:14:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Woman!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.48,0:14:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Are you listening?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.18,0:14:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Woman!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.15,0:14:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You underestimated me\Nbecause I'm a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.28,0:14:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a weak soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.32,0:14:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't kill bleeding hearts\Nor women.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.10,0:14:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.83,0:14:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.61,0:14:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Insulation section 2600.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.85,0:14:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Repairs are possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.75,0:14:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.45,0:14:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm calling you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.06,0:14:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why won't you even\Nacknowledge our kindness?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.39,0:14:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm being Mr. Nice Guy\Noffering to fix your suit...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.70,0:14:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,...but you brush me off!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.50,0:15:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want anybody\Ntouching my mobile suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.90,0:15:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.04,0:15:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a joke; you haven't\Neven got the parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.14,0:15:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The best engineers in the world\Ncan't do repairs without parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.11,0:15:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Mechanics need repair parts;\Nnot like you with your leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.88,0:15:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,See what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.19,0:15:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did I bother to rescue\Nthis guy in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.92,0:15:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He's anti-social, thinks he's\NEvel Knievel, and hardly speaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.39,0:15:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't take it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.29,0:15:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so gloomy; why not\Nstop pretending to be human?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.93,0:15:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.73,0:15:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.67,0:15:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You're too late to come\Nasking for my help!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.14,0:15:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you keep it down?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.51,0:15:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.54,0:15:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me for interrupting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.85,0:15:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.19,0:15:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.45,0:15:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,An enemy carrier's transporting\NGundanium alloy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.62,0:15:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.52,0:15:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.99,0:16:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you plan to work\Nwith your suit in this shape?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.96,0:16:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You're talking miracles!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.16,0:16:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd take a miracle for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.23,0:16:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.27,0:16:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well excuse me for being\Na mere mortal!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.14,0:16:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you screw up you'll\Nbe blown to bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.71,0:16:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Your missions have no\Nroom for failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.78,0:16:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like mine; the similarities\Nare uncanny!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.78,0:16:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Heero!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.25,0:16:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm right over here so\Nhurry and come kill me!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.20,0:16:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,According to reports from\NColonel Treize...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.40,0:16:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,...they're made of\NGundanium alloy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.50,0:16:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Very interesting...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.44,0:16:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,"Treize?!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.07,0:16:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Treize Khushrenada of\Nthe Specials?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.04,0:16:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard that Gundanium\Nalloy can only be refined...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.85,0:16:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,...in outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.75,0:16:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We should conclude that\Nthese mobile suits...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.65,0:16:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,...came from the colonies!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.99,0:17:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That'd mean disarming my\Nmilitary would be delayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.19,0:17:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we should be increasing\Nour presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.59,0:17:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd be glad to direct our\Ncountry's space forces...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.46,0:17:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,...to Lagrange Point and\Nsupport General Septem's troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.36,0:17:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Our nation has already made\Narrangements to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.33,0:17:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's unwise to interpret\Nthe actions of a few...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.14,0:17:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,...as reflecting all\Nthe colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.11,0:17:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The real problem is how to deal\Nwith these Gundam attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.64,0:17:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We know what the problem is!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.48,0:17:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,General, give orders to attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.31,0:17:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,More than anyone else,\Nthe colonies are hoping...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.35,0:17:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,...for peace in the Earth\NSphere Alliance!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.02,0:17:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We want peace as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.59,0:17:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The colonies' actions aren't\Nstemming from some jealousy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.96,0:17:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely not!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.26,0:17:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Until now hostilities have only\Nbeen sparked by attempts...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.40,0:17:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,...of the Alliance Military\Nto take control.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.40,0:17:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Your true feelings are\Nfinally emerging!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.63,0:17:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a spy and have been\Ncolluding with the colonies!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.47,0:17:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.30,0:17:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We've heard everything\Nyou have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.64,0:17:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like you to leave the room\Nnow, Vice Foreign Minister.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.74,0:17:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it about time you\Npeople realized...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.28,0:18:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,...that you're posing the\Ngreatest threat of all!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.75,0:18:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Silence! We've had enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.49,0:18:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So tension returns at\NLa Grange Point.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.92,0:18:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way it should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.43,0:18:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The leak worked well this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.43,0:18:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My hat's off to Zechs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.17,0:18:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He really did a fine job.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.30,0:18:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Lady Une.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.77,0:18:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.74,0:18:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,About Vice Foreign\NMinister Darlian...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.84,0:18:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll see to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.64,0:18:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll have rose fragrance\Nready for your next bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.71,0:18:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.83,0:18:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, what's he thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.26,0:18:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sacking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.32,0:19:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.35,0:19:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.86,0:19:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That guy's incredible; he\Nfixed his suit over night!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.23,0:19:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.63,0:19:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been had!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.76,0:19:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He took his parts\Nfrom this suit!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.10,0:19:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.53,0:19:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just complimenting him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.63,0:19:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Traitor!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.54,0:19:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Target confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.44,0:20:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost fixed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.98,0:20:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They're a similar make,\Nso it was pretty easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.68,0:20:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So similar it's freaky!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.35,0:20:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Right boss?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.58,0:20:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.35,0:20:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why Master Quatre\Nis so concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.99,0:20:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just relieved that this guy\Nwho can fight like Quatre...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.16,0:20:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,...isn't an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.64,0:21:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Noin, you all right in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.34,0:21:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.74,0:21:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Just feeling a little beat up\Ninside and out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.48,0:21:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Noin...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.88,0:21:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just happy you're alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.25,0:21:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if I died I'd get\Npromoted over you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.92,0:21:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got nothing to worry\Nabout with that sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.46,0:21:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs, you've gotta let me\Nfight the enemy with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.60,0:21:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna get stronger!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.83,0:21:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been through hell\Nwith that Gundam as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.97,0:21:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But next time they won't be\Ngetting off so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.71,0:21:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.01,0:21:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be happy if you\Nworked with me, Noin.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.04,0:21:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like that, Zechs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.85,0:22:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out of my sight,\Nyou weaklings!!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.49,0:22:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Fighting a weak enemy leaves\Nme feeling so empty afterward.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.06,0:22:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!!
